1
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:53,679
I'm worried about you.
That woman ghost might hurt you.

2
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:55,479
I can't promise you that.

3
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:57,880
- Why not?
- Because I'm worried about you too.

4
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:02,400
<i>But I have to find out</i>

5
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:06,040
who was the one
who ordered the murder of me...

6
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,839
Do you remember everything now, Sompong?

7
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:09,960
I remember!

8
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:15,920
This whore dares to steal my husband.

9
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,719
You dared to slap me?

10
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:21,040
Sir.

11
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:34,320
What's going on?

12
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:36,360
Hey, take her!

13
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:38,480
Come here!

14
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:41,279
- Come here!
- Let go!

15
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:43,200
- Let go of me!
- Don't struggle.

16
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:45,039
Stop.

17
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:46,400
What are you going to do?

18
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:51,760
You stopped your car just to help someone.
How generous of you.

19
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:54,080
I'll repay you

20
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:58,599
by taking your woman to heaven.
I hope you don't mind.

21
00:03:58,600 --> 00:03:59,640
Let go!

22
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:01,559
Come!

23
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:02,519
Let go!

24
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:03,719
Hey, no.

25
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:06,279
Let go! Mr. Phum!

26
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,759
Hey!

27
00:04:07,760 --> 00:04:09,320
Hold him!

28
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:37,840
Don't struggle.

29
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:47,400
I just slapped you
and you already fainted?

30
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:53,920
Good. Saves me the effort.

31
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:36,200
You evil bastard!

32
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:39,600
No! Don't come closer!

33
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:44,640
I'm scared!

34
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:03,760
Enough, please.

35
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:14,360
Enough!

36
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:22,360
Are you alright?

37
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,720
I'm alright.

38
00:06:26,320 --> 00:06:29,199
The police came to help me.
They're chasing those men right now.

39
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:30,560
Let's go.

40
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:31,960
Help me.

41
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:39,840
Criminals are almost as afraid
of the police as they are of ghosts.

42
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:41,960
What do you mean?

43
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:46,040
There aren't any police. I tricked them.

44
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:48,679
Some locals helped me.

45
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:52,000
They left before I could even thank them.

46
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:54,119
How are you?

47
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:56,360
I'm fine. Let's get out of here.

48
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:12,720
Luckily,
this room happened to be available.

49
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:15,280
You'll have to stay at my condo for now.

50
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:18,920
Will that be okay?

51
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:27,880
Thank you.
I've already troubled you enough as it is.

52
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:31,199
If you're hungry,
you can call and order food.

53
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,719
They'll deliver it.

54
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:35,199
There's also a minimart nearby.

55
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:37,439
If you need anything,
you can buy it there.

56
00:07:37,440 --> 00:07:39,240
If something happens, call me.

57
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:53,200
Take it. You'll need it.

58
00:07:54,400 --> 00:07:56,559
Once you remember everything,
you can pay me back

59
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:58,440
with interest, okay?

60
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:08,720
Thank you.

61
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:20,120
Don't forget. If you need anything,
call my number on the business card.

62
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:22,319
Okay.

63
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:23,280
I should get going now.

64
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:55,519
So much for acting all noble.

65
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:58,160
Turns out you've got a little mistress
hidden away in your condo too.

66
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:15,480
Hello. This is Phum Witasnai.

67
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,880
I contacted you regarding the exhibition.

68
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:22,200
Yes. I'm the one who postponed it
because of an emergency.

69
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:25,200
Would you be able
to prepare everything by next week?

70
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:33,600
Okay. That's alright.
I'll contact another company.

71
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,640
Would you like me to handle it for you?

72
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:42,560
I happen to own

73
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:45,039
a small events company.

74
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:47,799
But I assure you,
our skills are anything but small.

75
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:51,600
The International Flower Exhibition at
the convention center was my team's work.

76
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:54,879
Nice.

77
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:58,879
But I wouldn't dare hire your company.

78
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:00,960
My gallery opening is just a small event.

79
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:04,920
Excuse me.

80
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,239
What happened?

81
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:23,319
I think I sprained my ankle.

82
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:25,759
I was running after you.

83
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:27,719
Why would you be running after me?

84
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:31,560
Because I don't want to lose
a good friend like you.

85
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:36,000
I'm sorry. I'm the type of person
who speaks honestly.

86
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:39,880
That's good. I like speaking honestly too.

87
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:42,559
I don't want to get involved
with a woman who already has a boyfriend.

88
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:44,679
Not even as friends.

89
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,599
I don't think
your boyfriend will understand.

90
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,559
That's exactly

91
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:51,439
why I wanted to talk to explain it to you.

92
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:54,640
Prawin is only a friend.

93
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:57,759
But I hope you understand.

94
00:10:57,760 --> 00:11:01,280
What he feels for me
is something I can't control.

95
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:04,680
I think I understand.

96
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:09,720
Then we can be friends, right?

97
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:16,480
Your foot doesn't hurt anymore?

98
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:23,120
If I hadn't done that,
would you have stopped to talk to me?

99
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:47,559
May you have a safe journey.

100
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:48,520
Yes.

101
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:53,160
Kang, don't forget to feed the fish.

102
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,759
Yes, I won't.

103
00:11:55,760 --> 00:11:59,960
Since I don't have to bring food
to Uncle Sompong anymore.

104
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:02,600
Why not?

105
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:05,440
He's dead.

106
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:08,320
He burned to death in his hut.

107
00:12:11,360 --> 00:12:13,919
You should get going.

108
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:16,480
That way, you won't end up
traveling after dark.

109
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:21,920
Yes. Excuse us then.

110
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:49,360
What was that sound?

111
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:54,799
When you unloaded the offerings
for the Venerable Sir,

112
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:56,440
did you close the trunk properly?

113
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:08,360
I don't think it's the trunk.

114
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:10,160
Maybe

115
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:12,920
there's something back there.

116
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:37,320
I'm scared! No!

117
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:43,480
I'm scared!

118
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:46,759
No, I'm scared!

119
00:13:46,760 --> 00:13:48,360
How did Sompong end up here?

120
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:51,360
I thought they said he burned to death.

121
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:53,879
I'm scared!

122
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:56,600
Let's get him out first.

123
00:13:57,920 --> 00:13:59,159
- Sompong.
- Sompong.

124
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:01,079
Don't be afraid.

125
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:02,800
Sompong, don't be afraid.

126
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:07,440
- Don't.
- Come down first.

127
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:09,520
Sompong.

128
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:19,560
I don't know anything.

129
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:24,920
They told me to do it.

130
00:14:25,520 --> 00:14:27,120
A woman fell into the sea...

131
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,720
I don't know anything.

132
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:38,160
What is he talking about?

133
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:42,160
It's like somebody ordered him
to kill a woman.

134
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:49,239
Let's just take him back to the temple.

135
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:50,160
Wait.

136
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:58,840
Which woman?

137
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:09,960
What's her name?

138
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:14,280
Hey.

139
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,879
Why are you interrogating him?
He's unwell.

140
00:15:17,880 --> 00:15:20,359
He just rambles.

141
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:22,200
Maybe

142
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:25,680
there's a bit of truth
hidden inside the rambling.

143
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:29,040
And what are we supposed to do?

144
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:32,440
By now everyone probably thinks he's dead.

145
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:52,560
I think this outfit suits you well.

146
00:15:56,720 --> 00:16:00,720
I don't think it does.
It looks too nice for me.

147
00:16:01,440 --> 00:16:03,440
I like to wear something simple.

148
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:17,200
I'll look over there.

149
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:41,960
I think this outfit suits you well.

150
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:48,159
I think It's too nice for me.

151
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:52,080
I like to wear something simple.

152
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:59,640
Can I try jeans and T-shirts instead?

153
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:03,120
Go ahead.

154
00:17:09,480 --> 00:17:10,599
<i>Why are you smiling?</i>

155
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:13,119
Smiling?

156
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:17,039
Yes. You were grinning from ear to ear,

157
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:19,159
like someone who's incredibly happy.

158
00:17:19,160 --> 00:17:21,359
I didn't even realize
I was making such a fool of myself.

159
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:26,598
Not at all. When you smile,
you actually look much younger.

160
00:17:26,599 --> 00:17:30,839
When you compliment me to my face,
I never know how to react.

161
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:34,160
You've picked everything you like, right?

162
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:35,960
- Yes.
- Let's go.

163
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:40,480
Hello, Ms. Pat?

164
00:17:42,360 --> 00:17:44,519
Yes, I'm about to leave.

165
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:46,240
Let's meet at the condo.

166
00:17:56,320 --> 00:17:58,439
It's so nice to meet you, Ms. Pakarang.

167
00:17:58,440 --> 00:18:00,760
Mr. Phum's special someone.

168
00:18:03,240 --> 00:18:05,079
You've got the wrong idea.

169
00:18:05,080 --> 00:18:07,600
Ms. Pakarang
is only staying here temporarily.

170
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,439
I'm sorry.

171
00:18:10,440 --> 00:18:12,080
Sorry.

172
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:17,559
Why are your hands so cold?

173
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:19,040
Are you feeling sick?

174
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:21,000
Are you alright?

175
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:27,640
I'm alright.

176
00:18:28,160 --> 00:18:31,440
The air conditioning is very strong here.
I feel a little cold.

177
00:18:31,960 --> 00:18:34,160
I think I'll go upstairs.

178
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:38,519
You're not going to eat with us?

179
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:40,560
I'm not hungry yet.

180
00:18:41,640 --> 00:18:43,399
Are you sure?

181
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:44,480
Yes.

182
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:47,079
Then go get some rest.

183
00:18:47,080 --> 00:18:49,920
But if you feel sick, call me anytime.

184
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:51,840
Okay.

185
00:18:59,360 --> 00:19:01,960
Ms. Pakarang is very sweet.

186
00:19:02,720 --> 00:19:05,000
I felt an instant connection with her.

187
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:08,599
That's good.
Then she will have you as a friend.

188
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:09,679
I'd be delighted.

189
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:13,040
- Shall we get started on the event?
- Sure. Please excuse me.

190
00:19:23,240 --> 00:19:26,200
Mr. Phum, your dinner is ready.

191
00:19:27,520 --> 00:19:29,239
I haven't seen Sairung's car.
Hasn't she come home yet?

192
00:19:29,240 --> 00:19:31,360
No, sir.

193
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:34,759
But Mr. Narathon came back a while ago.

194
00:19:34,760 --> 00:19:37,239
He asked me to invite you
to the dining table.

195
00:19:37,240 --> 00:19:39,560
- Thon?
- Yes.

196
00:19:46,080 --> 00:19:48,680
Let's have dinner together, Dad.

197
00:19:52,360 --> 00:19:55,320
Of course. I was just getting hungry.

198
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,319
Serve the rice.

199
00:20:00,320 --> 00:20:02,040
Why are you just standing there?

200
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:11,919
Give me a lot of rice. I'm starving today.

201
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:12,840
Yes, sir.

202
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:21,920
I'm good.

203
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:24,559
Go do whatever you need to do.

204
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:27,160
I want to have dinner
with my father alone.

205
00:20:27,680 --> 00:20:28,920
Yes, sir.

206
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:33,879
We haven't had

207
00:20:33,880 --> 00:20:35,559
a nice atmosphere like this
in a long time.

208
00:20:35,560 --> 00:20:38,640
Eat up. Here's your favorite fried pork.

209
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:43,079
Remember when you were little?
You wouldn't eat anything else.

210
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:47,280
You kept asking for fried pork,
until your mom had to make it for you.

211
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:49,360
Try it.

212
00:20:59,520 --> 00:21:01,240
Where did Sarai disappear to?

213
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:16,240
Where is Sarai now?

214
00:21:23,680 --> 00:21:25,000
Why do you ask?

215
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:28,400
I just want to see her.

216
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:30,320
Why do you want to see her?

217
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:35,280
Even if you broke up with her,

218
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:39,240
she used to be my best friend.

219
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:42,919
You wouldn't mind

220
00:21:42,920 --> 00:21:45,240
if I contacted her and talked
to my best friend, would you?

221
00:21:52,320 --> 00:21:54,160
So where is Sarai?

222
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:57,040
I don't know.

223
00:21:58,280 --> 00:22:00,600
You don't know,
or you don't want to tell me?

224
00:22:27,760 --> 00:22:29,159
Mr. Phum.

225
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:32,280
What's wrong with you?
You look at me like you've seen a ghost.

226
00:22:34,120 --> 00:22:37,159
I didn't expect you
to be standing there so quietly.

227
00:22:37,160 --> 00:22:38,880
Where have you been?

228
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:44,080
I was bored,
so I stayed over with some friends.

229
00:22:45,320 --> 00:22:46,239
Why?

230
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:49,279
Normally, you never care.

231
00:22:49,280 --> 00:22:50,800
How strange.

232
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:53,359
Do you even care where I go?

233
00:22:53,360 --> 00:22:56,240
You look like someone
who went out and did something wrong.

234
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:02,960
The one who did something wrong

235
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:06,400
isn't me. It's you.

236
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:10,800
Fine. If you didn't do anything,
then you didn't.

237
00:23:11,560 --> 00:23:13,120
I have something to talk to you about.

238
00:23:15,080 --> 00:23:16,440
What is it about?

239
00:23:18,760 --> 00:23:19,760
Sarai.

240
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:22,640
What's going on?

241
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:25,959
Why are you saying her name?

242
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:29,840
You're the one who forbade me
from ever saying Sarai's name again.

243
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:38,320
Do not tell Narathon anything about Sarai.

244
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:41,680
Why?

245
00:23:42,480 --> 00:23:44,720
Is your son starting to suspect something?

246
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:47,080
When I give an order, you follow it.

247
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:51,200
If you still want to live comfortably
the way you do now.

248
00:24:40,440 --> 00:24:42,040
You seem different.

249
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:48,120
What are you going to start arguing
about now? Fine. Whatever makes you happy.

250
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:01,120
You really are different.

251
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:05,559
I'm still me.

252
00:25:05,560 --> 00:25:08,159
I just changed from a shirt
to a polo shirt,

253
00:25:08,160 --> 00:25:10,200
from slacks to jeans.
Is that really so strange?

254
00:25:17,640 --> 00:25:19,720
I've known you for ten years.

255
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:24,200
You only dress like this
when Sarai is around.

256
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:26,839
After she left,

257
00:25:26,840 --> 00:25:30,359
you became cold, slow to smile,
bad-tempered, unable to laugh.

258
00:25:30,360 --> 00:25:32,920
You could barely even
stand to look at my face.

259
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:36,240
Deny it. Tell me it isn't true.

260
00:25:37,840 --> 00:25:40,240
I don't want to argue with you
and ruin my morning.

261
00:25:40,920 --> 00:25:43,800
Think whatever you want.

262
00:25:58,400 --> 00:26:00,839
I'm very glad
to see all of you return safely.

263
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:03,519
And I must apologize
for sending help so late.

264
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:06,080
I never expected
something like this to happen.

265
00:26:08,320 --> 00:26:09,600
We understand.

266
00:26:10,960 --> 00:26:12,000
Thank you.

267
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:15,919
In that case,
from now on, Ms. Kaimook and Ms. Dara,

268
00:26:15,920 --> 00:26:17,360
please continue your internship.

269
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:24,359
What about what happened on the island?
Are we just going to let everything pass?

270
00:26:24,360 --> 00:26:28,520
Both we and the police are trying
to gather information from the past.

271
00:26:29,320 --> 00:26:32,480
But it really is strange.
There is no evidence at all.

272
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:38,680
I've tried looking too,
but I couldn't find anything either.

273
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:11,600
Good morning.

274
00:27:12,960 --> 00:27:13,880
Please come in.

275
00:27:21,280 --> 00:27:22,800
Is something wrong?

276
00:27:24,840 --> 00:27:27,320
- Yes.
- What is it?

277
00:27:28,720 --> 00:27:30,160
The way you're dressed.

278
00:27:33,920 --> 00:27:37,159
Why? Am I dressing too young for my age?

279
00:27:37,160 --> 00:27:40,000
At my age, I probably shouldn't
be wearing jeans anymore, right?

280
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:45,080
Not at all. I like you dressed like this.

281
00:27:46,120 --> 00:27:47,200
Really?

282
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:52,039
Yes. You look relaxed and approachable.

283
00:27:52,040 --> 00:27:56,080
That's a relief. I thought I was
trying too hard to look younger.

284
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:10,799
Mr. Thon,

285
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:13,760
Mook said you wanted to ask me something.

286
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:16,359
Yes.

287
00:28:16,360 --> 00:28:20,280
Did you see
the woman ghost's face clearly?

288
00:28:23,840 --> 00:28:25,800
I've seen her so many times
that I remember her now.

289
00:28:26,600 --> 00:28:28,120
Why?

290
00:28:31,280 --> 00:28:34,439
I want to know if the ghost

291
00:28:34,440 --> 00:28:36,760
is the woman in this photo?

292
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:52,720
You know this woman?

293
00:28:53,600 --> 00:28:55,399
You mean...

294
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:56,480
Yes.

295
00:28:58,160 --> 00:29:00,360
This woman is the ghost I saw.

296
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:08,520
Sarai...

297
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:19,520
Mr. Thon.

298
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:26,280
Mr. Narathon.

299
00:29:33,040 --> 00:29:33,880
Mr. Narathon.

300
00:29:35,720 --> 00:29:38,160
Are you alright?

301
00:29:39,720 --> 00:29:40,760
I'm fine.

302
00:29:44,360 --> 00:29:46,560
How do you know this woman?

303
00:29:47,480 --> 00:29:50,439
How did she die and...?

304
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:51,960
Thank you very much, Ms. Da.

305
00:29:52,480 --> 00:29:55,400
Kaimook. Please excuse me.

306
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:05,640
What's going on, Mook?

307
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:09,680
So Mr. Narathon knows that woman?
He even has photos with her.

308
00:30:13,720 --> 00:30:16,280
Or was she his ex-girlfriend?

309
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:23,959
It looks good.

310
00:31:23,960 --> 00:31:26,640
But normally, I only eat rice.

311
00:31:27,360 --> 00:31:29,559
Eating rice all the time is boring.

312
00:31:29,560 --> 00:31:32,080
Give it a try. I guarantee
you'll fall in love with my cooking.

313
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:36,760
I've never cooked for anyone before.

314
00:31:38,040 --> 00:31:39,919
- Really?
- Of course.

315
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:43,000
You're the first. And you'll be the last.

316
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:54,000
It's done.

317
00:31:58,880 --> 00:32:00,200
Why are you crying?

318
00:32:06,040 --> 00:32:07,080
Nothing.

319
00:32:09,720 --> 00:32:11,480
I'm just happy.

320
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:16,640
Well.

321
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:21,160
Even though I'm unlucky enough
to remember nothing,

322
00:32:24,560 --> 00:32:27,320
I was still fortunate enough
to meet someone kind like you

323
00:32:28,120 --> 00:32:29,760
who takes care of me.

324
00:32:31,440 --> 00:32:34,999
You're such a kid. I already told you

325
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:37,720
I'd take care of you
until your memory returns.

326
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:43,320
Dry your tears. Then let's eat.

327
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:27,160
Sarai?

328
00:33:36,160 --> 00:33:39,120
A life must be repaid with a life.

329
00:33:39,960 --> 00:33:43,200
No, Sarai. Don't.

330
00:34:12,239 --> 00:34:13,239
Sarai...

331
00:34:27,239 --> 00:34:28,320
Who's here?

332
00:34:31,320 --> 00:34:32,799
I'll go check.

333
00:34:32,800 --> 00:34:34,400
No, it's alright. I'll go.

334
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:37,120
Could you make me some coffee?

335
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:47,840
Ms. Pat?

336
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:51,158
I'm heading out to buy a few things.

337
00:34:51,159 --> 00:34:54,238
I just wanted to stop by
and ask if Ms. Pakarang needed anything.

338
00:34:54,239 --> 00:34:57,159
By the way, you're here so early.

339
00:34:57,160 --> 00:34:59,319
Thank you very much
for being so thoughtful toward Pakarang.

340
00:34:59,320 --> 00:35:01,839
It's nothing. But with you here,

341
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:05,639
I guess I don't need to worry.
In that case, I'll be going.

342
00:35:05,640 --> 00:35:06,999
Thank you again.

343
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:09,320
It's a small thing. Bye.

344
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:19,120
You're here morning and night and you're
still pretending there's nothing going on.

345
00:35:36,480 --> 00:35:37,879
Ms. Pat stopped by

346
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:39,680
to ask if you needed anything.

347
00:35:46,480 --> 00:35:47,600
Your coffee.

348
00:35:51,560 --> 00:35:53,560
Why did you make black coffee for me?

349
00:35:58,320 --> 00:35:59,240
Uh...

350
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:04,199
Well, I...
I guess I'm still a little confused.

351
00:36:04,200 --> 00:36:06,279
You told me to make coffee,

352
00:36:06,280 --> 00:36:09,240
so I only put in coffee and hot water.

353
00:36:10,720 --> 00:36:14,600
Oh right, coffee is supposed
to have sugar and creamer.

354
00:36:15,120 --> 00:36:16,360
I'm sorry.

355
00:36:16,880 --> 00:36:18,480
No need to apologize.

356
00:36:19,240 --> 00:36:21,160
I usually drink black coffee.

357
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:24,000
I was surprised that you knew that.

358
00:36:29,480 --> 00:36:33,040
I'm hungry.
Can I finally try your breakfast?

359
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:35,600
Sure. Be my guest.

360
00:37:04,680 --> 00:37:07,480
Mr. Narathon, it's me, Mook.

361
00:37:08,920 --> 00:37:10,160
May I come in?

362
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:14,200
Yes.

363
00:37:32,680 --> 00:37:34,120
I can't believe it.

364
00:37:37,320 --> 00:37:39,360
The ghost that asked Ms. Da for help...

365
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:45,080
The ghost that followed us
to Skull Island...

366
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:49,160
was Sarai.

367
00:37:57,840 --> 00:37:59,560
Who is Sarai?

368
00:38:00,400 --> 00:38:03,560
Would you mind telling me about her?

369
00:38:16,520 --> 00:38:17,560
- Mr. Phum.
- Hm?

370
00:38:20,400 --> 00:38:21,480
This is Sarai.

371
00:38:22,080 --> 00:38:24,840
I told you she lived near my old house.

372
00:38:27,920 --> 00:38:31,600
Sarai, greet Mr. Phum.
Mr. Phum is my husband.

373
00:38:33,320 --> 00:38:34,560
Good morning, sir.

374
00:38:43,280 --> 00:38:44,840
Mr. Narathon.

375
00:39:04,680 --> 00:39:07,120
You're so hardworking, Mr. Narathon.

376
00:39:13,320 --> 00:39:15,400
Are you unhappy that I'm staying here?

377
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:21,639
I won't cause any unnecessary trouble.

378
00:39:21,640 --> 00:39:24,760
I just want to continue my education.

379
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:30,280
I'll do any work in this house.
I can do everything.

380
00:39:33,600 --> 00:39:34,839
If you don't believe me,

381
00:39:34,840 --> 00:39:37,400
give me something to do.

382
00:39:43,520 --> 00:39:44,440
Alright.

383
00:39:45,600 --> 00:39:47,160
Then wash my car.

384
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:49,839
Make it shine.

385
00:39:49,840 --> 00:39:52,840
Let's see whether you're
really as capable as you claim.

386
00:39:58,240 --> 00:39:59,080
Wash a car?

387
00:40:01,560 --> 00:40:03,120
I just came back from a camp.

388
00:40:05,520 --> 00:40:06,640
So?

389
00:40:08,080 --> 00:40:09,200
You can't do it, right?

390
00:40:10,360 --> 00:40:11,360
Someone like you

391
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:17,280
probably dresses up nicely and charms
wealthy men into falling into your trap,

392
00:40:17,840 --> 00:40:19,200
just like Sairung.

393
00:40:21,120 --> 00:40:22,320
I can do it.

394
00:40:22,840 --> 00:40:26,279
I'll clean your car
so well you'll be amazed.

395
00:40:26,280 --> 00:40:28,520
Just wait and see.

396
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:05,200
What on earth are you doing?!

397
00:41:13,680 --> 00:41:14,879
I...

398
00:41:14,880 --> 00:41:18,080
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to do it.

399
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:23,360
Just leave. Go.

400
00:41:32,200 --> 00:41:33,840
I'm the one who should be upset.

401
00:41:34,680 --> 00:41:36,160
Why are you upset?

402
00:41:37,560 --> 00:41:41,919
I'm sorry. I just wanted to
continue my studies.

403
00:41:41,920 --> 00:41:45,359
I can wash it again.

404
00:41:45,360 --> 00:41:48,240
I'll also fix
the windshield wiper for you.

405
00:41:54,000 --> 00:41:55,719
- Give it to me.
- Sarai!

406
00:41:55,720 --> 00:41:56,959
- I'll fix it.
- Sarai!

407
00:41:56,960 --> 00:41:58,159
- Stop!
- I'll fix it.

408
00:41:58,160 --> 00:41:59,400
Give it to me. I'll fix it.

409
00:42:15,840 --> 00:42:17,080
Where are you going?

410
00:42:18,600 --> 00:42:20,279
To pack my things.

411
00:42:20,280 --> 00:42:21,520
Why?

412
00:42:22,320 --> 00:42:24,999
Because you don't like me.

413
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:28,280
You don't want me here. So I have to go.

414
00:42:30,040 --> 00:42:31,440
You can stay here.

415
00:42:33,680 --> 00:42:35,000
Really?

416
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:37,640
Yes.

417
00:42:39,200 --> 00:42:40,920
But never go near my car again.

418
00:42:43,280 --> 00:42:46,320
I promise. I won't go near your car again.

419
00:42:47,200 --> 00:42:48,239
I can stay here!

420
00:42:48,240 --> 00:42:51,239
I get to continue my studies! Thank you!

421
00:42:51,240 --> 00:42:53,560
<i>Sarai was so innocent</i>

422
00:42:55,560 --> 00:42:57,040
<i>that I couldn't help
feeling sorry for her.</i>

423
00:42:59,280 --> 00:43:01,280
<i>My initial dislike</i>

424
00:43:02,640 --> 00:43:04,920
<i>gradually turned into concern.</i>

425
00:43:07,600 --> 00:43:10,680
But when I saw the way
my father looked at her that day...

426
00:43:13,280 --> 00:43:17,120
The thing I feared would happen happened.

427
00:43:22,360 --> 00:43:23,480
You!

428
00:43:25,160 --> 00:43:26,400
What's going on?

429
00:43:27,560 --> 00:43:29,680
She tried to steal my husband.

430
00:43:31,200 --> 00:43:32,959
Stop.

431
00:43:32,960 --> 00:43:34,399
Stop right now, Sairung.

432
00:43:34,400 --> 00:43:37,000
If you lay a hand on Sarai again,
I won't let it slide.

433
00:43:38,640 --> 00:43:41,400
Of course. You've fallen for her.

434
00:43:42,200 --> 00:43:43,559
That's why you're protecting her so much.

435
00:43:43,560 --> 00:43:47,200
I haven't fallen for Sarai. I love her.

436
00:43:48,800 --> 00:43:50,240
Mr. Phum...

437
00:43:51,280 --> 00:43:53,800
After that, Sarai and I drifted apart.

438
00:43:55,760 --> 00:43:57,960
Then I went abroad.

439
00:43:59,000 --> 00:44:00,560
By the time I returned,

440
00:44:01,360 --> 00:44:03,240
Sarai was no longer living at the house.

441
00:44:05,600 --> 00:44:08,199
I asked my father and Sairung,

442
00:44:08,200 --> 00:44:10,200
but neither of them
wanted to talk about her.

443
00:44:11,480 --> 00:44:15,040
You think your father did it, right?

444
00:44:25,320 --> 00:44:26,280
Sarai.

445
00:44:27,720 --> 00:44:30,400
Sarai, you shameless woman.

446
00:44:32,680 --> 00:44:34,400
I want to kill you.

447
00:44:35,240 --> 00:44:36,880
I'll kill you, Sarai.

448
00:44:38,680 --> 00:44:39,880
All my life,

449
00:44:40,560 --> 00:44:42,840
I knew my father
had never been a good man.

450
00:44:44,520 --> 00:44:47,320
But I never thought
he could do something like this.

451
00:44:51,880 --> 00:44:53,400
I'll go talk to him.

452
00:44:55,720 --> 00:44:57,400
Wait.

453
00:45:13,520 --> 00:45:16,800
Are you telling me you love my daughter?

454
00:45:22,920 --> 00:45:23,760
You shameless woman.

455
00:45:33,560 --> 00:45:35,039
<i>I have a job for you.</i>

456
00:45:35,040 --> 00:45:38,320
<i>Easy work, quick money. Interested?</i>

457
00:46:13,320 --> 00:46:15,080
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
